The paper deals with computer-aided diagnosis (CAD) systems for skin lesion segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework employs deep learning techniques, specifically multi-stage UNets, which are commonly used in image segmentation tasks (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of context information fusion structure (CIFS) and deep supervision mechanism, which are techniques used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The dataset used in the experiments is the ISBI 2016 Skin Lesion Challenge dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
